The paper proposes a method for solving data-driven optimization problems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the method involves using model inversion networks (MINs), which are a type of neural network architecture. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using MINs for contextual bandit optimization from logged data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
